<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-09T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-09T12:00:00-05:00" n="149" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/9358</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GSU1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-09T18:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6.24 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2486. Your 920, June 18.<note n="1" xml:id="d149fn1">“Can you obtain
                                    copy German black list?”</note> Am hoping daily to secure copy
                                of German black list, but find much difficulty, owing to fear of
                                Danes that the firms mentioned might receive preferential treatment.
                                One list said to be in possession of the Stock Exchange and one with
                                the Chamber of Manufacturers.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GSU1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>